{"title_page": "C. N. Ahmad Moulavi", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name                    = C. N. Ahmad Moulavi\n| image                   = CN Ahmad Moulavi.jpg\n| imagesize               = \n| caption                 = \n| birth_date              = {{Birth year|1905}}\n| birth_place             = Cheroor, [[Eranad]], [[Malappuram district]], [[Kerala]], India\n| death_date              = {{Death date and age|df=yes|1993|4|27|1905|1|1}}\n| death_place             = [[Kozhikode]], Kerala\n| restingplace            =\n| restingplacecoordinates =\n| othername               =\n| occupation              = Essayist, translator, educationist, social reformer\n| alma mater              = \n| spouse                  = \n| domesticpartner         = \n| children                = \n| parents                 = {{ublist|Assan Kutty (father)|Khatheeja (mother)}}\n| influences              = \n| influenced              =\n| website                 = \n| awards                  = 1989&nbsp;[[Kerala Sahitya Akademi Fellowship]]\n}}\n'''C. N. Ahmad Moulavi''' (1905 \u2013 1993) was an Indian writer of [[Malayalam literature]], best known as the translator of the first complete publication of [[Quran]] in [[Malayalam]]. He was the author of a number of books on [[Islam]] and was reported to have contributed to the propagation of education among the Muslims of [[Malabar region]]. A member of the [[Kerala Sahitya Akademi]] during the period 1959\u201364, Moulavi was honoured by the academy with the [[Kerala Sahitya Akademi Fellowship|distinguished fellowship]] in 1989.\n\n== Biography ==\n[[File:Tomb of A'la Hadrat Shah Abdul Wahhab.jpg|left|thumb|Baqiyat Salihat Arabic College]]\nC. N. Ahmad Moulavi was born in 1905 at Cheroor, a village in [[Eranad]] in [[Malappuram district]] of the south Indian state of [[Kerala]] to Nathankodan Assan Kutty and Azhuvath Khatheeja.<ref name=\"Biography on Kerala Sahitya Akademi portal\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.keralasahityaakademi.org/sp/Writers/Profiles/CNAhmedMaulavi/Html/CNAMaulavigraphy.htm |title=Biography on Kerala Sahitya Akademi portal |date=2019-04-05 |website=Kerala Sahitya Akademi |access-date=2019-04-05}}</ref> Born in a family of poor financial means, he lost his father early and could have primary education for only three years after which he had to work in a farm for sustenance.<ref name=\"Miller2015\">{{cite book|author=Roland E. Miller|title=Mappila Muslim Culture: How a Historic Muslim Community in India Has Blended Tradition and Modernity|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XjSzCAAAQBAJ&pg=PA236|date=27 April 2015|publisher=SUNY Press|isbn=978-1-4384-5602-7|pages=236\u2013}}</ref> At the age of sixteen, he went back to studies, first at [[Karuvarakundu]] Grand Dars of Kunjalam Musaliar and later under Kattukandan Kunjahmed Musaliar.<ref name=\"Datta1987\">{{cite book|author=Amaresh Datta|title=Encyclopaedia of Indian Literature: A-Devo|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ObFCT5_taSgC&pg=PA106|year=1987|publisher=Sahitya Akademi|isbn=978-81-260-1803-1|pages=106\u2013}}</ref> This was followed by a short stints at the Madras Jamalia Arabic College and Bombay where he studied under K. T. Ibrahim Moulavi, only to proceed to [[Baqiyat Salihat Arabic College]], Vellore in 1928 from where he passed ''Afsal Ul Ulama'' examination in 1931. On his return to Kerala, he joined the Malappuram Training School as a religious instructor but resigned from the job in 1944 to start his own clothing business.<ref name=\"Miller2015\" />\n\nMoulavi started a magazine by name, ''Ansari'' which became defunct after publishing 14 issues; though he restarted the magazine under a new name, ''New Ansari'' in 1955, the publication did not last long.<ref name=\"Biography on Kerala Sahitya Akademi portal\" /> When the ''East Eranad Education Society'' was formed in 1964, Moulavi became the founder president of the society; the society, which started [[Dr. Gafoor Memorial MES Mampad College]] in 1965, was handed over the [[Muslim Educational Society]] (MES) in 1967.<ref name=\"MES Mampad College\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.mesmampad.org |title=MES Mampad College |date=2019-04-06 |website=mesmampad.org |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref>\n\nMaulavi died on 27 April 1993, at the age of 88, at [[Kozhikode]].<ref name=\"Biography on Kerala Sahitya Akademi portal\" />\n\n== Legacy and honours ==\nMaulavi published twelve books on Islamic studies, including a reportedly controversial book, ''Islamile Dhanavitharanapadhathi'' (Distribution of Wealth in Islam Tradition).<ref name=\"List of works\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.keralasahityaakademi.org/sp/Writers/Profiles/CNAhmedMaulavi/Html/CNAbdulmaulavibooks.htm |title=List of works |date=2019-04-05 |website=Kerala Sahitya Akademi |access-date=2019-04-05}}</ref> He was the first to publish a complete translation of the [[Quran]] into Malayalam<ref name=\"Kupferschmidt1987\">{{cite book|author=Uri M. Kupferschmidt|title=The Supreme Muslim Council: Islam Under the British Mandate for Palestine|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ChEVAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA462|year=1987|publisher=BRILL|isbn=90-04-07929-7|pages=462\u2013}}</ref> which he published in 1963,<ref name=\"C N Ahmed Maulavi: The Malayali Pioneer in Quran Translation\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4pcGd0FKHc0 |title=C N Ahmed Maulavi: The Malayali Pioneer in Quran Translation |last=MediaoneTV Live |date=2014-07-03 |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref> at a time when translation of Quran was considered a blasphemy.<ref name=\"Miller2015\" /> He wrote on many contentious issues such as divorce and maintenance among Muslims<ref name=\"Engineer2008\">{{cite book|author=Asgharali Engineer|title=The Rights of Women in Islam|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Q3uB_umOEbwC&pg=PA169|year=2008|publisher=Sterling Publishers Pvt. Ltd|isbn=978-81-207-3933-8|pages=169\u2013}}</ref> and his book, ''Mahathaya Mappila Sahitya Paramparyam'' (The glorious Mappila Literary Heritage)<ref name=\"Mahathaya Mappila Sahitya Paramparyam\">{{Cite web |url=https://kithabi.com/books/mahathaya-mappila-sahitya-paramparyam-%E0%B4%AE%E0%B4%B9%E0%B4%A4%E0%B5%8D%E0%B4%A4%E0%B4%BE%E0%B4%AF-%E0%B4%AE%E0%B4%BE%E0%B4%AA%E0%B5%8D%E0%B4%AA%E0%B4%BF%E0%B4%B3-%E0%B4%B8%E0%B4%BE%E0%B4%B9/ |title=Mahathaya Mappila Sahitya Paramparyam |date=2019-04-06 |website=kithabi.com |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref> is a comprehensive work on the Muslim literature in Kerala<ref name=\"Datta1987\" /><ref name=\"Mohammed2007\">{{cite book|author=U. Mohammed|title=Educational Empowerment of Kerala Muslims: A Socio-historical Perspective|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PCBdogPnnqsC&pg=PA30|year=2007|publisher=Other Books|isbn=978-81-903887-3-3|pages=30\u2013}}</ref> with details about the contribution of Muslims in the development of Arabic-Malayalam literature.<ref name=\"Contribution of Muslims in the Development of Malayalam Language and Literature\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ummid.com/news/2011/March/16.03.2011/contribution_of_muslims_fr_malayalam_lang.htm |title=Contribution of Muslims in the Development of Malayalam Language and Literature |website=www.ummid.com |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref> He served as a member of the [[Kerala Sahitya Akademi]] for five years from 1959 to 1964. In 1989, he was inducted as a [[Kerala Sahitya Akademi Fellowship|distinguished fellow]] by the [[Kerala Sahitya Akademi|academy]].<ref name=\"Kerala Sahitya Akademi Fellowship\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.keralasahityaakademi.org/sp/Writers/Fellows/Html/HonoraryList.htm |title=Kerala Sahitya Akademi Fellowship |date=2019-04-06 |website=Kerala Sahitya Akademi |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref> His birth centenary was celebrated in Kozhikode in 2005 and an exhibition of all his writings were organized as a part of it.<ref name=\"The Hindu : Kerala News : In remembrance\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.thehindu.com/2005/12/26/stories/2005122610910300.htm |title=The Hindu : Kerala News : In remembrance |website=www.thehindu.com |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref>\n\n== Bibliography ==\n{{Div col}}\n* {{Cite book |url=http://catalogue.mappilaheritagelibrary.com/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=1211&query_desc=au%253AC.N.%2520Ahmed%2520Moulavi |title=Parishudha Qur'an: Paribhashayum Vyakhyanavum Volume-1 |last=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi |date=1953 |publisher=Abdul Majeed Marikar |edition=1 |location=Perumbavoor}}\n* {{Cite book |url=http://103.251.43.202:8080/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=6830 |title=Parishudha Qur'an: Paribhashayum Vyakhyanavum Volume-2 |last=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi}}\n* {{Cite book |url=http://catalogue.mappilaheritagelibrary.com/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=1210&query_desc=au%253AC.N.%2520Ahmed%2520Moulavi |title=Parishudha Qur'an: Paribhashayum Vyakhyanavum Volume-3 |last=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi}}\n* {{Cite book |url=http://catalogue.mappilaheritagelibrary.com/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=1654&query_desc=au%253AC.N.%2520Ahmed%2520Moulavi |title=Islamika Sampathika Shasthram |last=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi |date=1954}}\n* {{Cite book |url=http://catalogue.mappilaheritagelibrary.com/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=1673&query_desc=au%253AC.N.%2520Ahmed%2520Moulavi |title=Qur'an: Enthu ? Enthinu ? |last=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi |date=1957}}\n* {{Cite book |url=http://catalogue.mappilaheritagelibrary.com/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=1702&query_desc=au%253AC.N.%2520Ahmed%2520Moulavi |title=Qur'an Krodeekaranam, Mansookh, Erinhukollal: Moonnu Vambicha Thettidharanakal |last=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi |publisher=C.N. Ahmed Moulavi |edition=1 |location=Chevayur, Kozhikode}}\n* {{Cite book |url=https://find.uoc.ac.in/Record/169772/Description |title=Mahathaya Mappila Sahitya Parampariam |last=C.N |first=Ahmmed Moulavi |last2=K.K. |first2=Muhammed Abdulkareem |date=1978}}<ref name=\"OPS123\">{{cite book |last1=Salahudheen, O P |title=Anti_European struggle by the mappilas of Malabar 1498_1921 AD |page=123 |url=https://sg.inflibnet.ac.in/bitstream/10603/52423/12/12_chapter%204.pdf#page=22 |accessdate=14 November 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"MB264\">{{cite book |last1=Mumtas Begum A.L. |title=Muslim women in Malabar Study in social and cultural change |page=264 |url=https://sg.inflibnet.ac.in/bitstream/10603/19904/13/13_select%20bibliography.pdf#page=6 |accessdate=11 November 2019}}</ref>)\n* {{Cite book |title=Manu\u1e63hya Jeevitha\u1e43 Ana\u015bvara\u1e43 |last=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi |date=1983 |publisher=Azad Book Stall |location=Calicut |language=Malayalam |oclc=17149726}}\n* {{Cite book |title=Isl\u0101\u1e43 charitr\u0332a\u1e43 |last=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi |date=1971 |publisher=Ans\u0101ri Press |location=Calicut |language=Malayalam |oclc=30629062}}\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== Translations into other languages ===\n* {{cite book|author=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi|title=Religion of Islam: A Comprehensive Study|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZBVYNAAACAAJ|year=1979|publisher=Azad Book Stall}}\n* {{cite book|author=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi|title=Principles and practice of Islamic Economy|url=http://103.251.43.202:8080/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=86544|year=1964|publisher=Ansari press}}\n\n== See also ==\n{{Div col|colwidth=40em}}\n* [[List of Malayalam-language authors by category]]\n* [[List of Malayalam-language authors]]\n{{div col end}}\n{{Portal|India|Literature}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* {{Cite web |url=http://muslimheritage.in/innermore/138 |title=History Conference |last=VM.Safir  |website=muslimheritage.in |access-date=2019-04-06}}\n* {{Cite web |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2017/oct/22/who-decides-halal-and-haraam-malayalam-actor-mamukkoya-slams-growing-intolerance-1679893.html |title=Who decides Halal and Haraam? Malayalam actor Mamukkoya slams growing intolerance |website=The New Indian Express |access-date=2019-04-06}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Cite web |url=http://www.keralasahityaakademi.org/sp/Writers/Profiles/CNAhmedMaulavi/Html/CNAhmedmaulavi.htm |title=Portrait commissioned by Kerala Sahitya Akademi |date=2019-04-05 |website=Kerala Sahitya Akademi |access-date=2019-04-05}}\n* {{Cite web |url=http://www.keralasahityaakademi.org/sp/Writers/Fellows/CNAMaulavi/CNAhmedMaulavi.htm |title=Conferring Fellowship |date=2019-04-06 |website=Kerala Sahitya Akademi |access-date=2019-04-06}}\n* {{Cite web |url=http://archive.org/details/EncyclopaediaDictionaryIslamMuslimWorldEtcGibbKramerScholars.13 |title=Encyclopaedia Dictionary Islam Muslim World, etc, Gibb, Kramer, scholars. 13 vols & 12 vols. 1960-2004.1875.2009. |last=Oriental Scholars: Gibb |first=Kramer |date=2019-04-06 |access-date=2019-04-06}}\n* {{Cite web |url=https://www.scribd.com/document/108473688/Maasappiravi-From-Samagra-Padanam-book-CN-Ahmed-Moulavi |title=Maasappiravi - From Samagra Padanam book - CN Ahmed Moulavi |website=Scribd |language=en |access-date=2019-04-06}}\n* {{Cite web |url=https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Search/Home?lookfor=%2522Ahmad%2520Maulavi,%2520Si.%2520En.%2522&type=author&inst= |title=Catalog Search Results - Hathi Trust Digital Library |website=catalog.hathitrust.org |access-date=2019-04-06}}\n\n{{Kerala Sahitya Akademi Fellowship}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Moulavi, C. N. Ahmad}}\n[[Category:1905 births]]\n[[Category:1993 deaths]]\n[[Category:Writers from Kerala]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian essayists]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Kerala Sahitya Akademi Award]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian translators]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian historians]]\n[[Category:Indian Islamists]]\n[[Category:People from Malappuram district]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian educators]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name                    = C. N. Ahmad Moulavi\n| image                   = CN Ahmad Moulavi.jpg\n| imagesize               = \n| caption                 = \n| birth_date              = {{Birth year|1905}}\n| birth_place             = Cheroor, [[Eranad]], [[Malappuram district]], [[Kerala]], India\n| death_date              = {{Death date and age|df=yes|1993|4|27|1905|1|1}}\n| death_place             = [[Kozhikode]], Kerala\n| restingplace            =\n| restingplacecoordinates =\n| othername               =\n| occupation              = Essayist, translator, educationist, social reformer\n| alma mater              = \n| spouse                  = \n| domesticpartner         = \n| children                = \n| parents                 = {{ublist|Assan Kutty (father)|Khatheeja (mother)}}\n| influences              = \n| influenced              =\n| website                 = \n| awards                  = 1989&nbsp;[[Kerala Sahitya Akademi Fellowship]]\n}}\n'''C. N. Ahmad Moulavi''' (1905 \u2013 1993) was an Indian writer of [[Malayalam literature]], best known as the translator of the first complete publication of [[Quran]] in [[Malayalam]]. He was the author of a number of books on [[Islam]] and was reported to have contributed to the propagation of education among the Muslims of [[Malabar region]]. A member of the [[Kerala Sahitya Akademi]] during the period 1959\u201364, Moulavi was honoured by the academy with the [[Kerala Sahitya Akademi Fellowship|distinguished fellowship]] in 1989.\n\n== Biography ==\n[[File:Tomb of A'la Hadrat Shah Abdul Wahhab.jpg|left|thumb|Baqiyat Salihat Arabic College]]\nC. N. Ahmad Moulavi was born in 1905 at Cheroor, a village in [[Eranad]] in [[Malappuram district]] of the south Indian state of [[Kerala]] to Nathankodan Assan Kutty and Azhuvath Khatheeja.<ref name=\"Biography on Kerala Sahitya Akademi portal\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.keralasahityaakademi.org/sp/Writers/Profiles/CNAhmedMaulavi/Html/CNAMaulavigraphy.htm |title=Biography on Kerala Sahitya Akademi portal |date=2019-04-05 |website=Kerala Sahitya Akademi |access-date=2019-04-05}}</ref> Born in a family of poor financial means, he lost his father early and could have primary education for only three years after which he had to work in a farm for sustenance.<ref name=\"Miller2015\">{{cite book|author=Roland E. Miller|title=Mappila Muslim Culture: How a Historic Muslim Community in India Has Blended Tradition and Modernity|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XjSzCAAAQBAJ&pg=PA236|date=27 April 2015|publisher=SUNY Press|isbn=978-1-4384-5602-7|pages=236\u2013}}</ref> At the age of sixteen, he went back to studies, first at [[Karuvarakundu]] Grand Dars of Kunjalam Musaliar and later under Kattukandan Kunjahmed Musaliar.<ref name=\"Datta1987\">{{cite book|author=Amaresh Datta|title=Encyclopaedia of Indian Literature: A-Devo|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ObFCT5_taSgC&pg=PA106|year=1987|publisher=Sahitya Akademi|isbn=978-81-260-1803-1|pages=106\u2013}}</ref> This was followed by a short stints at the Madras Jamalia Arabic College and Bombay where he studied under K. T. Ibrahim Moulavi, only to proceed to [[Baqiyat Salihat Arabic College]], Vellore in 1928 from where he passed ''Afsal Ul Ulama'' examination in 1931. On his return to Kerala, he joined the Malappuram Training School as a religious instructor but resigned from the job in 1944 to start his own clothing business.<ref name=\"Miller2015\" />\n\nMoulavi started a magazine by name, ''Ansari'' which became defunct after publishing 14 issues; though he restarted the magazine under a new name, ''New Ansari'' in 1955, the publication did not last long.<ref name=\"Biography on Kerala Sahitya Akademi portal\" /> When the ''East Eranad Education Society'' was formed in 1964, Moulavi became the founder president of the society; the society, which started [[Dr. Gafoor Memorial MES Mampad College]] in 1965, was handed over the [[Muslim Educational Society]] (MES) in 1967.<ref name=\"MES Mampad College\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.mesmampad.org |title=MES Mampad College |date=2019-04-06 |website=mesmampad.org |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref>\n\nMaulavi died on 27 April 1993, at the age of 88, at [[Kozhikode]].<ref name=\"Biography on Kerala Sahitya Akademi portal\" />\n\n== Legacy and honours ==\nMaulavi published twelve books on Islamic studies, including a reportedly controversial book, ''Islamile Dhanavitharanapadhathi'' (Distribution of Wealth in Islam Tradition).<ref name=\"List of works\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.keralasahityaakademi.org/sp/Writers/Profiles/CNAhmedMaulavi/Html/CNAbdulmaulavibooks.htm |title=List of works |date=2019-04-05 |website=Kerala Sahitya Akademi |access-date=2019-04-05}}</ref> He was the first to publish a complete translation of the [[Quran]] into Malayalam<ref name=\"Kupferschmidt1987\">{{cite book|author=Uri M. Kupferschmidt|title=The Supreme Muslim Council: Islam Under the British Mandate for Palestine|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ChEVAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA462|year=1987|publisher=BRILL|isbn=90-04-07929-7|pages=462\u2013}}</ref> which he published in 1963,<ref name=\"C N Ahmed Maulavi: The Malayali Pioneer in Quran Translation\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4pcGd0FKHc0 |title=C N Ahmed Maulavi: The Malayali Pioneer in Quran Translation |last=MediaoneTV Live |date=2014-07-03 |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref> at a time when translation of Quran was considered a blasphemy.<ref name=\"Miller2015\" /> He wrote on many contentious issues such as divorce and maintenance among Muslims<ref name=\"Engineer2008\">{{cite book|author=Asgharali Engineer|title=The Rights of Women in Islam|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Q3uB_umOEbwC&pg=PA169|year=2008|publisher=Sterling Publishers Pvt. Ltd|isbn=978-81-207-3933-8|pages=169\u2013}}</ref> and his book, ''Mahathaya Mappila Sahitya Paramparyam'' (The glorious Mappila Literary Heritage)<ref name=\"Mahathaya Mappila Sahitya Paramparyam\">{{Cite web |url=https://kithabi.com/books/mahathaya-mappila-sahitya-paramparyam-%E0%B4%AE%E0%B4%B9%E0%B4%A4%E0%B5%8D%E0%B4%A4%E0%B4%BE%E0%B4%AF-%E0%B4%AE%E0%B4%BE%E0%B4%AA%E0%B5%8D%E0%B4%AA%E0%B4%BF%E0%B4%B3-%E0%B4%B8%E0%B4%BE%E0%B4%B9/ |title=Mahathaya Mappila Sahitya Paramparyam |date=2019-04-06 |website=kithabi.com |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref> is a comprehensive work on the Muslim literature in Kerala<ref name=\"Datta1987\" /><ref name=\"Mohammed2007\">{{cite book|author=U. Mohammed|title=Educational Empowerment of Kerala Muslims: A Socio-historical Perspective|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PCBdogPnnqsC&pg=PA30|year=2007|publisher=Other Books|isbn=978-81-903887-3-3|pages=30\u2013}}</ref> with details about the contribution of Muslims in the development of Arabic-Malayalam literature.<ref name=\"Contribution of Muslims in the Development of Malayalam Language and Literature\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ummid.com/news/2011/March/16.03.2011/contribution_of_muslims_fr_malayalam_lang.htm |title=Contribution of Muslims in the Development of Malayalam Language and Literature |website=www.ummid.com |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref> He served as a member of the [[Kerala Sahitya Akademi]] for five years from 1959 to 1964. In 1989, he was inducted as a [[Kerala Sahitya Akademi Fellowship|distinguished fellow]] by the [[Kerala Sahitya Akademi|academy]].<ref name=\"Kerala Sahitya Akademi Fellowship\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.keralasahityaakademi.org/sp/Writers/Fellows/Html/HonoraryList.htm |title=Kerala Sahitya Akademi Fellowship |date=2019-04-06 |website=Kerala Sahitya Akademi |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref> His birth centenary was celebrated in Kozhikode in 2005 and an exhibition of all his writings were organized as a part of it.<ref name=\"The Hindu : Kerala News : In remembrance\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.thehindu.com/2005/12/26/stories/2005122610910300.htm |title=The Hindu : Kerala News : In remembrance |website=www.thehindu.com |access-date=2019-04-06}}</ref>\n\n== Bibliography ==\n{{Div col}}\n* {{Cite book |url=http://catalogue.mappilaheritagelibrary.com/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=1211&query_desc=au%253AC.N.%2520Ahmed%2520Moulavi |title=Parishudha Qur'an: Paribhashayum Vyakhyanavum Volume-1 |last=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi |date=1953 |publisher=Abdul Majeed Marikar |edition=1 |location=Perumbavoor}}\n* {{Cite book |url=http://103.251.43.202:8080/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=6830 |title=Parishudha Qur'an: Paribhashayum Vyakhyanavum Volume-2 |last=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi}}\n* {{Cite book |url=http://catalogue.mappilaheritagelibrary.com/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=1210&query_desc=au%253AC.N.%2520Ahmed%2520Moulavi |title=Parishudha Qur'an: Paribhashayum Vyakhyanavum Volume-3 |last=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi}}\n* {{Cite book |url=http://catalogue.mappilaheritagelibrary.com/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=1654&query_desc=au%253AC.N.%2520Ahmed%2520Moulavi |title=Islamika Sampathika Shasthram |last=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi |date=1954}}\n* {{Cite book |url=http://catalogue.mappilaheritagelibrary.com/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=1673&query_desc=au%253AC.N.%2520Ahmed%2520Moulavi |title=Qur'an: Enthu ? Enthinu ? |last=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi |date=1957}}\n* {{Cite book |url=http://catalogue.mappilaheritagelibrary.com/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=1702&query_desc=au%253AC.N.%2520Ahmed%2520Moulavi |title=Qur'an Krodeekaranam, Mansookh, Erinhukollal: Moonnu Vambicha Thettidharanakal |last=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi |publisher=C.N. Ahmed Moulavi |edition=1 |location=Chevayur, Kozhikode}}\n* {{Cite book |url=https://find.uoc.ac.in/Record/169772/Description |title=Mahathaya Mappila Sahitya Parampariam |last=C.N |first=Ahmmed Moulavi |last2=K.K. |first2=Muhammed Abdulkareem |date=1978}}<ref name=\"OPS123\">{{cite book |last1=Salahudheen, O P |title=Anti_European struggle by the mappilas of Malabar 1498_1921 AD |page=123 |url=https://sg.inflibnet.ac.in/bitstream/10603/52423/12/12_chapter%204.pdf#page=22 |accessdate=14 November 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"MB264\">{{cite book |last1=Mumtas Begum A.L. |title=Muslim women in Malabar Study in social and cultural change |page=264 |url=https://sg.inflibnet.ac.in/bitstream/10603/19904/13/13_select%20bibliography.pdf#page=6 |accessdate=11 November 2019}}</ref>)\n* {{Cite book |title=Manu\u1e63hya Jeevitha\u1e43 Ana\u015bvara\u1e43 |last=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi |date=1983 |publisher=Azad Book Stall |location=Calicut |language=Malayalam |oclc=17149726}}\n* {{Cite book |title=Isl\u0101\u1e43 charitr\u0332a\u1e43 |last=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi |date=1971 |publisher=Ans\u0101ri Press |location=Calicut |language=Malayalam |oclc=30629062}}\n{{div col end}}\n\n=== Translations into other languages ===\n* {{cite book|author=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi|title=Religion of Islam: A Comprehensive Study|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZBVYNAAACAAJ|year=1979|publisher=Azad Book Stall}}\n* {{cite book|author=C. N. Ahmed Moulavi|title=Principles and practice of Islamic Economy|url=http://103.251.43.202:8080/cgi-bin/koha/opac-detail.pl?biblionumber=86544|year=1964|publisher=Ansari press}}\n\n== See also ==\n{{Div col|colwidth=40em}}\n* [[List of Malayalam-language authors by category]]\n* [[List of Malayalam-language authors]]\n{{div col end}}\n{{Portal|India|Literature}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* {{Cite web |url=http://muslimheritage.in/innermore/138 |title=History Conference |last=VM.Safir  |website=muslimheritage.in |access-date=2019-04-06}}\n* {{Cite web |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2017/oct/22/who-decides-halal-and-haraam-malayalam-actor-mamukkoya-slams-growing-intolerance-1679893.html |title=Who decides Halal and Haraam? Malayalam actor Mamukkoya slams growing intolerance |website=The New Indian Express |access-date=2019-04-06}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Cite web |url=http://www.keralasahityaakademi.org/sp/Writers/Profiles/CNAhmedMaulavi/Html/CNAhmedmaulavi.htm |title=Portrait commissioned by Kerala Sahitya Akademi |date=2019-04-05 |website=Kerala Sahitya Akademi |ac